      <Node id="042ffdff-bd69-449a-aeb7-9b48231e5cb5" name="CP-9 (6): REDUNDANT SECONDARY SYSTEM" success="AND">
        <Node id="23bb76a7-ca7f-4957-93a5-2acc2b42ca58" name="The organization accomplishes information system backup by maintaining a redundant secondary system that is not collocated with the primary system and that can be activated without loss of information or disruption to operations." />
      </Node>
      <Node id="afbf93c9-f1fe-4084-ad16-518697c50d73" name="CP-9 (7): DUAL AUTHORIZATION" description="Dual authorization ensures that the deletion or destruction of backup information cannot occur unless two qualified individuals carry out the task. Individuals deleting/destroying backup information possess sufficient skills/expertise to determine if the proposed deletion/destruction of backup information reflects organizational policies and procedures. Dual authorization may also be known as two-person control." success="AND">
